dt: {bc}a lettuce that belongs to a cultivar of garden lettuce ({it}Lactuca sativa{/it}) and has long crisp leaves and columnar heads

et: French, from feminine of {it}romain{/it} Roman, from Old French, from Latin {it}Romanus{/it}
shortdef: a lettuce that belongs to a cultivar of garden lettuce (Lactuca sativa) and has long crisp leaves and columnar heads —called also cos lettuce
